column7: How Daniel landed his first $10k client
column9:
Back in January 2023, Daniel started his ghostwriting business.

At the time (and to this day), Daniel is our Chief Operations
Officer and the Email Marketing Wizard behind Ship 30 for 30 and
Premium Ghostwriting Academy.

So, with his wealth of experience, he thought landing his first
ghostwriting client would be easy.

He started to do what everyone does:

* Found his ideal clients
* Sent them a cold DM
* And followed up regularly

But after a few weeks, Daniel had to face a brutal truth:

His approach wasn’t working.
----------------------------

After sending hundreds of DMs, with little to no response, Daniel
was ready to give up.

But Daniel KNEW he could help the people he was targeting, so he
needed a new way to get their attention.

He had to rethink his entire approach to landing clients.

And it paid off.

It’s how Daniel landed his first $10,000 client:
------------------------------------------------

​

----------
Cha-ching!
----------

​
So, what did he do differently?

First, he stopped sending blanket DMs and personalized every
message he sent.

But he also needed a way to get the potential client to message
him back and agree to work with him.

So, in his outreach message, he offered to do some free work.
-------------------------------------------------------------

His “Free Offer” needed to be so good, that people would feel
stupid saying “no.”

With this Daniel could:

* Get his foot in the door
* Overdeliver with free value
* Help them solve another problem in their business (which he
could charge for)

So, Daniel started to build his Free Offer:

* This is something he would normally do as part of his full
service/package/offer—but is still valuable on its own
* It’s small enough that he could fulfill it in a few days but
meaningful enough that the client actually wants it
* And something most of his ideal clients need or want (so he
could systematize it and do it repeatedly)

So after reviewing his offer stack and doing some research,
Daniel created his first Free Offer:

A free segmentation survey implementation.

And it worked for 3 reasons:

* Reason #1: This was something he was already planning on doing
as part of his full package. Even if they didn’t end up hiring
him to build the whole thing, they could still benefit from it.
​
* Reason #2: It would only take him a few days to implement it.
So if needed, he could do several of these every month. But the
prospect would be able to immediately see the value.
​
* Reason #3: It was a piece most of his dream clients were
missing in their funnel. And he knew that, with some education,
he could easily “sell” them on the idea.

After less than a week using this new approach, Daniel got his
first “yes.”

Daniel hopped on a call with the client and then got to work. He
did everything he could to delight the client.

And once he was done fulfilling on his free offer, guess what the
client said:

“This is epic. What else can you help me with? I’d love to keep
working together.”
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Two weeks later, he paid Daniel $10,000 to build and ghostwrite
an end-to-end lead magnet funnel for him.

This is the exact outreach strategy we teach inside the Premium
Ghostwriting Academy, and Daniel nailed it. Since then, Daniel’s
used this approach to land all his outbound clients.

And we keep seeing this strategy work over and over again inside
PGA (even for people who have never ghostwritten for anyone
before, like Lane here):

​
Now, Daniel and Lane might be outliers… but we know this
framework and approach works because it’s how I scaled my
ghostwriting agency to $180k/month in less than 18 months (and I
started from zero!).

So, do you want the exact blueprint to land your first
high-ticket client?
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Then this will mean investing in yourself.

I’ve taught this strategy (and every pillar of becoming a Premium
Ghostwriter) to over 1,000 people in PGA—and the results have
been incredible to see.

Hello Candace,

Congrats on finishing the 5-day Generative AI Intensive course! As we wrapthings up, this is our final round up of reminders and announcements.

📋 Reminders and Announcements


🎯 Capstone Project: Level up your skills and enhance your portfolio with areal-world capstone project. You'll create a notebook showcasing a use casethat leverages some of the key generative AI capabilities learnedthroughout this course. For bonus points, you'll have the option to createa blog post and/or YouTube video around your use case. The top 10 winnerswill have their work featured on Kaggle and Google Cloud's social media.Additional details about the capstone project, evaluation, and submissionprocess will be shared in another email today. Participation in thecapstone project is optional.
⭐ Kaggle badge and certificate: You are eligible to earn a badge andcertificate on your Kaggle profile for participating in the capstoneproject. The badges and certificates will be added to your profile by theend of April 2025.
👀 Look out for the Kaggle Learn Guide: All of the course content will beaggregated and made publicly available next week as a handy Kaggle LearnGuide. We'll share it with you as soon as it's ready. In the meantime, allof the livestream recordings can be found here.
🎟️ Google Cloud NEXT: If you happen to be at Google Cloud NEXT this year,don't forget to drop by at the “Become a GenAI Expert” session led by PaigeBailey and Anant Nawalgaria. We will also be giving out limited copies ofthe abridged whitepapers at the Coding Challenge hub. We hope to see youthere!
📢 Share your feedback: Please fill out this quick feedback form to let usknow more about your experience. It'll help us improve the program forfuture participants. Your feedback is completely anonymous and should onlytake a few minutes.

And with that, thank you very much for joining us this week. We enjoyedconnecting with you all, and wish you nothing but the best as you continueto grow your skills in this field.

Cheers,

The Kaggle Team

Hey, Candace...

 

5 years ago I started the Jay Shetty Certification School with one mission:

 

Create a global network of specially trained, holistic coaches who work together to change 1 billion lives.

 

And to date we’ve trained over 3,100 new coaches to do that. 🎉

 

They’re working around the world, creating real transformation.

 

But…

 

The need for these coaches is also growing much faster than we expected.

 

Especially right now when people are feeling so uncertain about their jobs and their future…

 

And the world around us is so chaotic.

 

We need to step up our efforts.

 

So every family can have a coach to give them hope, support, and guidance.

 

That’s why I’m sending you this special Anniversary invitation letter (please read it before Sunday) ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/5-years/?el=5th-bday-email-158-1&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+158-1&utm_content_name=Invitation+for+Name+%E2%9C%89%EF%B8%8F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ).

 

It’s only going out to a special group of my followers.

 

The people who read my emails every week…

 

Who share our passion for helping others…

 

And want to be part of our mission for 2025.

 

If that sounds like you, Candace…

 

Read my special 5th Anniversary invitation letter now. ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/5-years/?el=5th-bday-email-158-1&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+158-1&utm_content_name=Invitation+for+Name+%E2%9C%89%EF%B8%8F&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )
